post.description:
Validate EQL syntax and get a cost estimate without creating a query.
Returns simulation-based cost details when the query is valid.

### Required Sequence (Enforced)

`POST /v2/auto/queries/validate` must be called before
`POST /v2/auto/queries`.

Lifecycle sequencing after create:
1. `POST /v2/auto/queries/{queryId}/cancel` while status is
   `active`.
2. `DELETE /v2/auto/queries/{queryId}` only after status is terminal
   (`triggered`, `expired`, `cancelled`, `failed`).

### Cost

Free.

### Auth

Required header:
```http
x-elfa-api-key: <api_key>
```

HMAC signing is not required for validate.

### Request Example

```json
{
  "query": {
    "conditions": {
      "AND": [
        {
          "source": "price",
          "method": "current",
          "args": { "symbol": "BTC" },
          "operator": ">",
          "value": 100000
        }
      ]
    },
    "actions": [
      {
        "stepId": "step_1",
        "type": "notify",
        "params": { "message": "BTC crossed target" }
      }
    ],
    "expiresIn": "24h"
  },
  "title": "BTC breakout alert",
  "description": "Notify when BTC is above 100k so I can review the breakout setup."
}
```

### Response Example (200)

```json
{
  "valid": true,
  "errors": [],
  "warnings": [],
  "simulationLlmCallsEstimate": {
    "conditionCallsUpperBound": 1,
    "actionCallsUpperBound": 0,
    "conditionCallsBySpeed": { "fast": 1, "expert": 0 },
    "actionCallsBySpeed": { "fast": 0, "expert": 0 }
  },
  "estimatedCost": {
    "credits": 30,
    "price": "$0.270"
  }
}
```

> Best practice: always validate before create to catch schema issues and
> preview estimated cost.
